  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "presented MacBERT [138] (MLM as a correction) model as a pretrained model.",
    "The model improves RoBERTa from several aspects, such as reducing the gap between the pretraining and the fine-tuning phases by masking similar words.",
    "It also replaces the NSP pretraining task with the SOP in ALBERT.",
    "In addition, BERT has been pretrained on biomedical [48] and clinical [29] data to achieve state-of-the-art performance across biomedical tasks [43].To balance efficiency and effectiveness, Hofstätter et al.",
    "proposed the transformer-kernel (TK) model [105,106] that improves the architecture of the KNRM [18]."
  ],
